GROOKEY.description:
When it uses its special stick to strike up
a beat, the sound waves produced carry
revitalizing energy to the plants and
flowers in the area.

THWACKEY.description: The faster a Thwackey can beat out\na rhythm with its two sticks, the more\nrespect it wins from its peers.

RILLABOOM.description: By drumming, it taps into the power of\nits special tree stump. The roots of the\nstump follow its direction in battle.

GMAX.description: Rillaboom has become one with its\nforest of drums and continues to lay\ndown beats that shake all of Galar.

SCORBUNNY.description:
A warm-up of running around gets fire
energy coursing through this Pokémon's
body. Once that happens, it's ready to
fight at full power.

RABOOT.description: Its thick and fluffy fur protects it\nfrom the cold and enables it to use\nhotter fire moves.

CINDERACE.description:
It juggles a pebble with its feet,
turning it into a burning soccer ball.
Its shots strike opponents hard and
leave them scorched.

GMAX.description:
Infused with Cinderace's fighting
spirit, the gigantic Pyro Ball never
misses its targets and completely
roasts opponents.

SOBBLE.description:
When scared, this Pokémon cries.
Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100
onions, and attackers won't be
able to resist weeping.

DRIZZILE.description: A clever combatant, this Pokémon battles\nusing water balloons created with\nmoisture secreted from its palms.

INTELEON.description:
It has many hidden capabilities, such as
fingertips that can shoot water and a
membrane on its back that it can use to
glide through the air.

GMAX.description:
Gigantamax Inteleon's Water Gun
move fires at Mach 7. As the Pokémon
takes aim, it uses the crest on its
head to gauge wind and temperature.

SKWOVET.description: Found throughout the Galar region, this\nPokémon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are\never completely empty of berries.

GREEDENT.description:
It stashes berries in its tail--so many
berries that they fall out constantly.
But this Pokémon is a bit slow-witted,
so it doesn't notice the loss.

ROOKIDEE.description:
It will bravely challenge any opponent,
no matter how powerful. This Pokémon
benefits from every battle--even a
defeat increases its strength a bit.

CORVISQUIRE.description:
Smart enough to use tools in battle,
these Pokémon have been seen picking up
rocks and flinging them or using ropes
to wrap up enemies.

CORVIKNIGHT.description:
This Pokémon reigns supreme in the skies
of the Galar region. The black luster of
its steel body could drive terror into
the heart of any foe.

GMAX.description:
Imbued with Gigantamax energy, its
wings can whip up winds more
forceful than any a hurricane could
muster. The gusts blow everything away.

BLIPBUG.description: A constant collector of information,\nthis Pokémon is very smart. Very strong\nis what it isn't.

DOTTLER.description:
It barely moves, but it's still alive.
Hiding in its shell without food or
water seems to have awakened its
psychic powers.

ORBEETLE.description:
It's famous for its high level of
intelligence, and the large size of its
brain is proof that it also possesses
immense psychic power.

GMAX.description:
Its brain has grown to a gargantuan
size, as has the rest of its body.
This Pokémon's intellect and
psychic abilities are overpowering.

NICKIT.description:
Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it
silently raids the food stores of other
Pokémon. It survives off its
ill-gotten gains.

THIEVUL.description:
It secretly marks potential targets with
a scent. By following the scent, it
stalks its targets and steals from them
when they least expect it.

GOSSIFLEUR.description:
It anchors itself in the ground with its
single leg, then basks in the sun. After
absorbing enough sunlight, its petals
spread as it blooms brilliantly.

ELDEGOSS.description:
The seeds attached to its cotton fluff
are full of nutrients. It spreads them
on the wind so that plants and other
Pokémon can benefit from them.

WOOLOO.description:
Its curly fleece is such an effective
cushion that this Pokémon could fall off
a cliff and stand right back up at the
bottom, unharmed.

DUBWOOL.description:
Weave a carpet from its springy wool,
and you end up with something closer to
a trampoline. You'll start to bounce the
moment you set foot on it.

CHEWTLE.description: Apparently the itch of its teething\nimpels it to snap its jaws at anything\nin front of it.

DREDNAW.description: With jaws that can shear through steel\nrods, this highly aggressive Pokémon\nchomps down on its unfortunate prey.

GMAX.description:
In the Galar region, there's a tale
about this Pokémon chewing up a
mountain and using the rubble to stop a
flood.

YAMPER.description:
This Pokémon is very popular as a
herding dog in the Galar region. As it
runs, it generates electricity from the
base of its tail.

BOLTUND.description:
This Pokémon generates electricity and
channels it into its legs to keep them
going strong. Boltund can run nonstop
for three full days.

ROLYCOLY.description:
Most of its body has the same composition
as coal. Fittingly, this Pokémon was
first discovered in coal mines about
400 years ago.

CARKOL.description: It forms coal inside its body. Coal\ndropped by this Pokémon once helped fuel\nthe lives of people in the Galar region.

COALOSSAL.description:
It's usually peaceful, but the vandalism
of mines enrages it. Offenders will be
incinerated with flames that reach
2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

GMAX.description:
Its body is a colossal stove. With
Gigantamax energy stoking the fire,
this Pokémon's flame burns hotter
than 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

APPLIN.description:
It spends its entire life inside an
apple. It hides from its natural enemies,
bird Pokémon, by pretending it's just an
apple and nothing more.

FLAPPLE.description: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its\nevolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid\ncapable of causing chemical burns.

GMAX.description:
Under the influence of Gigantamax
energy, it produces much more sweet
nectar, and its shape has changed
to resemble a giant apple.

APPLETUN.description: Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution.\nA nectarous scent wafts from its body,\nluring in the bug Pokémon it preys on.

GMAX.description:
Due to Gigantamax energy, this
Pokémon's nectar has thickened. The
increased viscosity lets the nectar
absorb more damage than before.

DIPPLIN.description: Dipplin is two creatures in one Pokémon.\nIts evolution was triggered by a special\napple grown only in one place.

HYDRAPPLE.description:
These capricious syrpents have
banded together. On the rare
occasion that their moods align,
their true power is unleashed.

SILICOBRA.description: As it digs, it swallows sand and stores\nit in its neck pouch. The pouch can hold\nmore than 17 pounds of sand.

SANDACONDA.description:
When it contracts its body, over 220
pounds of sand sprays from its nose. If
it ever runs out of sand, it becomes
disheartened.

GMAX.description:
Its sand pouch has grown to tremendous
proportions. More than 1,000,000 tons of
sand now swirl around its body with enough
speed and power to pulverize a skyscraper.

CRAMORANT.description: It's so strong that it can knock out some\nopponents in a single hit, but it also may\nforget what it's battling midfight.

GULPING.description:
Cramorant's gluttony led it to try
to swallow an Arrokuda whole, which
in turn led to Cramorant getting an
Arrokuda stuck in its throat.

GORGING.description:
This Cramorant has accidentally
gotten a Pikachu lodged in its gullet.
Cramorant is choking a little, but it
isn't really bothered.

ARROKUDA.description:
If it sees any movement around it, this
Pokémon charges for it straightaway,
leading with its sharply pointed jaw.
It's very proud of that jaw.

BARRASKEWDA.description:
This Pokémon has a jaw that's as sharp
as a spear and as strong as steel.
Apparently Barraskewda's flesh is
surprisingly tasty, too.

TOXEL.description:
It stores poison in an internal poison
sac and secretes that poison through its
skin. If you touch this Pokémon, a
tingling sensation follows.

TOXTRICITY_AMPED.description:
When this Pokémon sounds as if it's
strumming a guitar, it's actually clawing
at the protrusions on its chest to
generate electricity.

TOXTRICITY_LOW_KEY.description: Capable of generating 15,000 volts\nof electricity, this Pokémon looks\ndown on all that would challenge it.

SIZZLIPEDE.description: It stores flammable gas in its body and\nuses it to generate heat. The yellow\nsections on its belly get particularly hot.

CENTISKORCH.description:
When it heats up, its body temperature
reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit.
It lashes its body like a whip and
launches itself at enemies.

GMAX.description:
The heat that comes off a
Gigantamax Centiskorch may
destabilize air currents. Sometimes
it can even cause storms.

CLOBBOPUS.description:
It's very curious, but its means of
investigating things is to try to punch
them with its tentacles. The search for
food is what brings it onto land.

GRAPPLOCT.description: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes\nthe grappling moves this Pokémon performs\nwith its tentacles tremendously powerful.

SINISTEA_PHONY.description: This Pokémon is said to have been born\nwhen a lonely spirit possessed a cold,\nleftover cup of tea.

SINISTEA_ANTIQUE.description:
The swirl pattern in this Pokémon's
body is its weakness. If it gets
stirred, the swirl loses its shape, and
Sinistea gets dizzy.

POLTEAGEIST_PHONY.description: This species lives in antique teapots.\nMost pots are forgeries, but on rare\noccasions, an authentic work is found.

POLTEAGEIST_ANTIQUE.description:
Trainers Polteageist trusts will be
allowed to experience its
distinctive flavor and aroma firsthand by
sampling just a tiny bit of its tea.

HATENNA.description:
Via the protrusion on its head, it senses
other creatures' emotions. If you don't
have a calm disposition, it will never
warm up to you.

HATTREM.description: No matter who you are, if you bring strong\nemotions near this Pokémon, it will silence\nyou violently.

HATTERENE.description: It emits psychic power strong enough to\ncause headaches as a deterrent to the\napproach of others.

GMAX.description:
This Pokémon can read the
emotions of creatures over 30 miles away.
The minute it senses hostility, it
goes on the attack.

IMPIDIMP.description:
Through its nose, it sucks in the
emanations produced by people and
Pokémon when they feel annoyed. It
thrives off this negative energy.

MORGREM.description:
When it gets down on all fours as if to
beg for forgiveness, it's trying to lure
opponents in so that it can stab them
with its spear-like hair.

GRIMMSNARL.description: With the hair wrapped around its body\nhelping to enhance its muscles, this\nPokémon can overwhelm even Machamp.

GMAX.description:
Gigantamax energy has caused more
hair to sprout all over its body.
With the added strength, it can jump
over the world's tallest building.

MILCERY.description: This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling\nparticles in the air. Its body is made\nof cream.

ALCREMIE_GMAX.description:
It launches swarms of missiles,
each made of cream and loaded with
100,000 kilocalories. Get hit by one of
these, and your head will swim.

FALINKS.description: Five of them are troopers, and one is the\nbrass. The brass's orders are absolute.

MEGA.description:
Mega Falinks has taken on the
ultimate battle formation, which
can be achieved only if the troopers
and brass have the strongest of bonds.

PINCURCHIN.description: It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to\nscrape it off rocks. Electric current\nflows from the tips of its spines.

SNOM.description:
It spits out thread imbued with a frigid
sort of energy and uses it to tie its body
to branches, disguising itself as an
icicle while it sleeps.

FROSMOTH.description:
Icy scales fall from its wings like snow
as it flies over fields and mountains.
The temperature of its wings is less than
-290 degrees Fahrenheit.

STONJOURNER.description:
It stands in grasslands, watching the
sun's descent from zenith to horizon. This
Pokémon has a talent for delivering
dynamic kicks.

EISCUE_ICE.description:
It drifted in on the flow of ocean waters
from a frigid place. It keeps its head
iced constantly to make sure it stays
nice and cold.

EISCUE_NOICE.description:
The hair on its head connects to
the surface of its brain. When this
Pokémon has something on its mind,
its hair chills the air around it.

INDEEDEE_F.description:
They diligently serve people and
Pokémon so they can gather feelings
of gratitude. The females are
particularly good at babysitting.

INDEEDEE_M.description:
It uses the horns on its head to sense the
emotions of others. Males will act as
valets for those they serve, looking
after their every need.

MORPEKO_HANGRY.description:
Intense hunger drives it to
extremes of violence, and the electricity
in its cheek sacs has converted into
a Dark-type energy.

MORPEKO_FULL_BELLY.description:
As it eats the seeds stored up in its
pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not
just satisfying its constant hunger. It's
also generating electricity.

CUFANT.description:
It digs up the ground with its trunk.
It's also very strong, being able to
carry loads of over five tons without any
problem at all.

COPPERAJAH.description: They came over from another region long\nago and worked together with humans.\nTheir green skin is resistant to water.

GMAX.description:
After this Pokémon has Gigantamaxed,
its massive nose can utterly demolish
large structures with a single
smashing blow.

DRACOZOLT.description:
In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks
to its powerful lower body, but it went
extinct anyway after it depleted all its
plant-based food sources.

ARCTOZOLT.description: The shaking of its freezing upper half is\nwhat generates its electricity. It has a\nhard time walking around.

DRACOVISH.description:
Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex
predator of its time. Its own overhunting
of its prey was what drove it to
extinction.

ARCTOVISH.description:
Though it's able to capture prey by
freezing its surroundings, it has trouble
eating the prey afterward because its
mouth is on top of its head.

DURALUDON.description: Its body resembles polished metal, and\nit's both lightweight and strong. The only\ndrawback is that it rusts easily.

GMAX.description:
The hardness of its cells is
exceptional, even among Steel types. It
also has a body structure that's
resistant to earthquakes.

ARCHALUDON.description:
It gathers static electricity
from its surroundings. The beams
it launches when down on all fours
are tremendously powerful.

DREEPY.description:
After being reborn as a ghost Pokémon,
Dreepy wanders the areas it used to
inhabit back when it was alive in
prehistoric seas.

DRAKLOAK.description: It's capable of flying faster than 120 mph.\nIt battles alongside Dreepy and dotes\non them until they successfully evolve.

DRAGAPULT.description:
When it isn't battling, it keeps Dreepy
in the holes on its horns. Once a fight
starts, it launches the Dreepy like
supersonic missiles.

ZACIAN_HERO.description: Known as a legendary hero, this Pokémon\nabsorbs metal particles, transforming\nthem into a weapon it uses to battle.

ZACIAN_CROWNED.description:
Able to cut down anything with a
single strike, it became known as the
Fairy King's Sword, and it inspired
awe in friend and foe alike.

ZAMAZENTA_HERO.description:
In times past, it worked together with a
king of the people to save the Galar
region. It absorbs metal that it then
uses in battle.

ZAMAZENTA_CROWNED.description:
Its ability to deflect any attack
led to it being known as the Fighting
Master's Shield. It was feared and
respected by all.

ETERNATUS.description:
The core on its chest absorbs energy
emanating from the lands of the Galar
region. This energy is what allows
Eternatus to stay active.

ETERNAMAX.description:
As a result of Rose's meddling,
Eternatus absorbed all the energy in
the Galar region. It's now in a state
of power overload.

KUBFU.description: Kubfu trains hard to perfect its moves.\nThe moves it masters will determine which\nform it takes when it evolves.

URSHIFU_RAPID_STRIKE.description:
This form of Urshifu is a strong
believer in defeating foes by raining
many blows down on them. Its
strikes are nonstop, flowing like a river.

URSHIFU_SINGLE_STRIKE.description:
This form of Urshifu is a strong believer
in the one-hit KO. Its strategy is to leap
in close to foes and land a devastating
blow with a hardened fist.

URSHIFU_SINGLE_STRIKE_GMAX.description:
People call it the embodiment of
rage. It's said that this Pokémon's
terrifying expression and shout will
rid the world of malevolence.

GMAX.description:
As it waits for the right moment to
unleash its Gigantamax power, this
Pokémon maintains a perfect one-
legged stance. It won't even twitch.

ZARUDE.description:
Within dense forests, this Pokémon lives
in a pack with others of its kind. It's
incredibly aggressive, and the other
Pokémon of the forest fear it.

DADA.description:
This Zarude's special strength
stems from its love and care for an
orphaned human child that the Pokémon
has raised.

REGIELEKI.description:
This Pokémon is a cluster of electrical
energy. It's said that removing the rings
on Regieleki's body will unleash the
Pokémon's latent power.

REGIDRAGO.description:
An academic theory proposes that
Regidrago's arms were once the head of an
ancient dragon Pokémon. The theory
remains unproven.

GLASTRIER.description: Glastrier emits intense cold from its\nhooves. It's also a belligerent Pokémon--\nanything it wants, it takes by force.

SPECTRIER.description:
It probes its surroundings with all its
senses save one--it doesn't use its sense
of sight. Spectrier's kicks are said to
separate soul from body.

CALYREX.description:
Calyrex is a merciful Pokémon, capable of
providing healing and blessings. It
reigned over the Galar region in times
of yore.

ICE.description:
According to lore, this Pokémon
showed no mercy to those who got in
its way, yet it would heal its
opponents' wounds after battle.

SHADOW.description:
It's said that Calyrex and a
Pokémon that had bonded with it ran all
across the Galar region to bring green
to the wastelands.

ENAMORUS_THERIAN.description:
From the clouds, it descends upon
those who treat any form of life
with disrespect and metes out
wrathful, ruthless punishment.

ENAMORUS_INCARNATE.description:
Its arrival brings an end to the winter.
According to legend, this Pokémon's love
gives rise to the budding of fresh life
across the land.
